<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB07912</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT REGULATING THE CATCHING SALE, PURCHASE, POSSESSION, TRANSPORTATION, IMPORTATION, AND EXPORTATION OF ALL SHARKS, RAYS, CHIMAERAS, OR ANY PART THEREOF IN THE COUNTRY</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Provides for the conservation and protection of sharks, management of their threats, and creation of shark sanctuaries. Declares the following acts as illegal and penalizes the same: killing, taking, keeping in captivity, inflicting injury, harassing and trading vulnerable, threatened, endangered, or critically endangered species, and finning  of sharks, among others.  </td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : “Shark Conservation Act of the Philippines.”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>MACAPAGAL ARROYO, GLORIA</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-07-09</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Biazon (000 2018-09-03)</td><td>2. Olivarez (000 2018-09-04)</td><tr><td>3. Fortun (000 2018-09-24)</td><td>4. Tambunting (000 2018-09-27)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>MOTHER BILL:&nbspHB08926</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON NATURAL RESOURCES ON 2018-07-30</td></tr></table>